## How the Pre-Commit Hook Generates This File

```bash
# From 01-project-contract.md, Section C:
git log --oneline -10 > .ai-context/session-context.md
echo "Last updated: $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)" >> .ai-context/session-context.md
echo "Changed files (staged): $(git diff --name-only --cached | wc -l | tr -d ' ') files" >> .ai-context/session-context.md
```

The "Active Tasks" and "Blocked Items" sections are preserved across hook runs
because the hook only overwrites the top commit-log section, not the whole file.
If you need to reset the file, delete it — the next commit will recreate it.
